commitResults.messageTitle: Change example output and better error handling
commitResults.messageBody:
Example output when receiving an invalid status command was wrong. Now, changed to the correct example.

Previously, typing "status 1" did not correctly give an invalid command. Now, it will output an "Invalid command" and show an example usage.

UI for adding a person is implemented in this commit.

Functionality is minimal -- you can type text into each of the boxes, but submitting does nothing for now.
Pressing cancel will hide the window and reset all fields, so this works as intended.

The next step would be to properly handle a submit request. Right now, it just hides the window.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add prompt text into text fields
commitResults.messageBody: Prompt text added to text fields in order to aid the user

It is now possible to add people through AddWindow.

However, the result of adding is not displayed in MainWindow.
Result of successfully/failing to add a person into ModuleMateFinder will be displayed on MainWindow's Ui.

When a person has a particular status, it will show their corresponding image.

If a person has no status, then a placeholder (fully transparent) is used instead.

Giving an invalid tag when using the filter command did not display an error message in the ResultDisplay box.

After merging, this will be displayed properly.

Remove extra portion in AboutUs

Update my own PPP

When a user types "add", instead of showing an error message, it will now open up AddWindow.

This is similar to the behaviour of typing 'help' in the CommandBox.

At the last `TextField`, pressing `ENTER` key submits the fields in AddWindow.

AddWindow's functionality (for adding more fields) will be extended further, to do more commands.

Some of the commands that will be implemented:
- addmodule
- status

These will allow for users to input the modules of the contact that they are adding, and their status.

It is possible to add modules, and a person's corresponding status.

The logic is not finalised yet and there may still be some changes.

With this current implementation, a `Person` is added even if the optional fields result in an error (e.g. `status` not being `blacklist` or `favourite`, or a `Module` being of the wrong format).

A new idea to improve on this would be to prevent anything from being executed if it results in an error; so user has to fix all errors before `AddWindow` executes and closes.

I will probably change to the above soon.
Short circuits if any of the optional fields are not empty, and are of invalid syntax.

Update UG to include AddWindow within the add command.

Also fixed some errors within the UG.

commitResults.messageBody: Move block of function to below for better logical flow as well.
EditWindow is a quick and easy way for users to edit any person within ModuleMate Finder.
Typing `edit` will open up `EditWindow` instead of throwing an error.

Important:
Removed assertParseFailure() in `EditCommandParserTest` as having no index and no field being specified will no longer result in a `ParseFailure`, but will open up `EditWindow` instead.
New field added, so new check needs to be implemented.

Use a factory method to get a new instance of an empty `EditCommand`. This is a safer way of instantiating the empty `EditCommand`, and prevents users from unintentionally creating an empty `EditCommand` as it should only be used for `EditWindow`.
Combine `AddWindow.css` and `EditWindow.css` into one CSS file, `AdditionalWindow.css` as there is high reusability.
